==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''though'', [[thoh]], borrowed from a Scandinavian source such as Old Norse [[þó]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]] /ðoʊ/ (''US''); /ðoʊ/ (''UK'')
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] /DoU/

===Conjunction===
#despite the fact that; [[although]].
#:''Though it's risky, it's worth taking the chance.''
#:''I will not go there if I'm not secure, though.''

